.<br><br>Dr. Ted Taylor does not buy that view. He considers a rapid nuclear reaction that releases energy with a greater than 1 gain (output to input)  as most definitely a nuclear explosion. He led a lawsuit against NIF on those grounds, but since the CTBT was not ratified, I don't think thats still active. Dunno.<br><br>yale<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cattlecar>cattlecar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/1/02 8:58:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~macami/ez/spinthingie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: interpetation of the nuclear test ban treaty</span><hr size=1> Yales is on to something.  Nuclear explosions are allowed <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> if</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>they occur underground.  What are the possibilities that a cannon type<br>device be built, the breech is placed underground, the muzzle above. <br>The projectile is cargo intended for space.  A huge hollow metal<br>sphere is located aft of the breech, with a funnel into it. The<br>breech end has a moving metal pusher plate.  Now detonate a series of <br>small nukes inside the sphere. The plasma is funneled into the breech,<br>and pushes the plate up the cannon barrel.  In front of the pusher<br>plate is the space bound cargo.  The pusher plate accelerates up the<br>cannon barrel, but is stopped near the end of the muzzle to prevent<br>the release of radioactive plasma (plasma could be re-routed back to<br>the sphere). The cargo is released at the end of the muzzle and a<br>small rocket motor takes over for the rest of